headline: Usher Says He Was Misunderstood And Passed Over In School — Now He's Worth $200 Million And Tells Gen Z 'Blaze A New Trail'
summary: "Blaze a new trail," singer-songwriter Usher Terry Raymond IV urged Emory University's Class of 2025 during his commencement address on May 12 in Atlanta, stressing that "it's the person who animates the degree." The eight-time Grammy winner received an honorary doctor of humane letters during the speech, where he recalled being "misunderstood and passed over" in school yet still amassing an estimated $200 million fortune through music, tech bets, and sports ownership.
